        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-25 19:05:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nShould test_33a and test_33b be moved over to sanityn.sh, where they are much more likely to be run by developers?\n\nAlso, for the create_remote_dir() function, please do not use postional parameters, especially not positional parameters that depend on how many arguments are passed. Instead it would be easy to check:\n\n        if [ \"$1\" = \"-i\" ]; then\n                mkdir -p $(dirname $3)\n                $LFS mkdir -i $2 $3\n        else\n                mkdir -p $3\n        fi\n\nOr something similar without adding complex parsing or usage.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
