        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-18 20:22:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(16 inline comments)\n\nA bunch of cleanups possible, but most of them are not directly related to the patch itself.\n\nMy one main question is whether the tests in this script are exercising the DLM code handling the two separate LOOKUP locks that are needed for remote entries (one on the FID for each of the parent and remote MDTs)?  I recall discussing this in the past, but I don't recall enough of the details to know for sure if this is being tested.\n\nIf yes, it would be useful to add a small comment block to the specific test(s) to explain how this is being tested, since it is quite subtle.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "3e37e2674d08063bc4677b73a825be78ddfb01df",
      "author": {
